-- Egypt Military Train Derailment Kills at Least 19, MENA Reports
-- B y   Z a i d   S a b a h
-- 2013-01-15T02:17:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/egypt-military-train-derailment-kills-at-least-19-mena-reports.html
A military train heading from Cairo
to Sinai derailed near the Giza neighborhood of Badrashin early
today, leaving at least 19 dead and 107 injured, the state-run
 Middle East News Agency  reported, citing Ahmed Omar, a spokesman
for the health ministry.  The train was carrying 1,328 young recruits when the
incident took place shortly after midnight, Ahram Gate said,
citing security officials.  The incident comes less than two months after around 50
children were killed when their bus was hit by a train as it
drove over a railway crossing in the Assiut village of
Manfalout, Upper  Egypt , Ahram Gate said  To contact the reporter on this story:
